(7) In financing arrangement, a financial institution provides a cost plus mark up financing facility allowed by the bank of Tanzania that enables a person to acquire goods or assets from a vendor through a financial institution:

(a) The financial institution shall be deemed not to have acquired or supplied goods under this financing arrangement; (b) The customer shall be deemed to have acquired goods, from the seller for consideration equal to the amount paid by the financial institution direct to the seller; (c) Any profit paid or payable to the financial institution by the customer shall be seemed to be consideration in respect of an exempt financial service supplied by the financial institution”.

(8) The Minister may make Regulations for collection and calculation of Value Added Tax in the supply of financial services.

17 Time of supply.

